\%} — that take much more time and experience to master. Our cars have gotten much better at detecting and responding to everything from crossing guards to emergency vehicles to construction zones. With these advanced driving skills, we can adjust to things like sudden changes in road conditions, such as closed lanes. The ability to navigate smoothly on the road, while subtle, is also an important advanced driving skill that helps people feel comfortable whether they're inside or outside of the car. With each mile we drive, our test drivers provide feedback on the car's movements — things like how quickly we accelerate and brake, the distance we keep from other cars and pedestrians, or the speed and angle we turn. With each piece of feedback, our engineers tweak our software and calibrate our driving behavior, making our self-driving car feel more natural on the road. We have a better understanding of the social side of driving. Ultimately, being a good driver is about understanding other people — pedestrians, bikers and fellow drivers. Over the last year, we've learned that being a good driver is more than just knowing how to safely navigating around people, but also knowing how to interact with them.},
